Write a program which does the following

Find out and display the area of a rectangle of sides 45 and 76 respectively.
Declare variables 
ℎ
length, 
ℎ
width and 
area and assign the relevant values to them
Make sure to add some text, so that the person reading the output knows what the output means.
Output Format
The Area of the given rectangle is {
area

Sol.:-

#include<stdio.h>

int main() {

int length = 45; // Here, length is a container of number or a variable which holds 45 digit inside it //
int width = 76;
int area = length * width;

printf("The Area of the given rectangle is %d", area);
return 0;
}
